\bI am the Energy Guru! I sell only the most mystical of items!
\rI am the X-Queen! I sell only the most X of items!
\rI am the Misc Mistress! I sell only the most Misc of items!
\bWhat was that creepy Giratina-looking guy all about? He's not a cultist- there aren't any Giratina cults as far as I know- so I don't get why you'd dress up like that.
\bWelcome, traveler! You've come just in time to see Narra Town's annual Trainers Market!
\bYou'll be able to find the most splendiferous of items here.
\rOh gosh, there are so many things to buy and so little time. What do I get? What do I get?

\rYou see that pathway off to the east?
\rYou know where that goes? The freakin Pokemon league. That's right.
\rYou gotta have all your badges of course though. And nobody has eight anymore, which sucks.
\bWe've had trainer after trainer come through here, ready to end their adventure on Victory Road, and be turned away by the guards.
\bThe First Augur's gone! There's no eighth badge for anyone.
\bI mean, it's probably for the best.
\bI don't think anyone would be able to beat our Elite Four, anyways.
\bI could swear I saw a rare dragon Pokemon flying over Narra Town earlier.
\bIt looked... blue? And it was trailed by a similar red one a minute later.
\bNo, there's no way. Those Pokemon are only from Hoenn. Right?
\rDo you want a gift? I have a couple of nice stones to give away...
\rYou know, if you were planning on giving one of those to an Eevee...
\rMake sure you're sure about doing it! You never know what options may open up later on!
\rI hope that stone helps you out!
\rOne of my friends over in Hekate Town has been freaking out about spiders.
\rYou might want to give him a hand. I'm sure he could use the help.
